 metadata, stats, and dynamic-access report in this repository. \"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:1984:    if candidate.reason == \"test_generation_failed\" or candidate.coverage is None:\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:1992:        \"This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\n\\n\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:1994:        \"- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\n\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2140:        \"Inspect the available logs, generated tests, Gradle output, and metrics. \"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2273:    if candidate.reason in {\"test_generation_failed\", \"job_failed\"}:\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2406:        f\"ai/{authenticated_login}/human-intervention/\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2490:    \"\"\"Refresh library logs on an already pushed human-intervention branch.\"\"\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2535:    \"\"\"Post the human-intervention comment and always attempt to apply the label.\"\"\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2544:                f\"ERROR: Failed to post human-intervention comment to issue #{issue_number}: {exc!r}\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2565:    \"\"\"Post a human-intervention comment and label when an issue run needs follow-up.\"\"\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2583:            f\"ERROR: Failed to apply human-intervention follow-up to issue #{claimed_issue.issue['number']}: {exc!r}\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4444:            \"Forwarded to the new-library pipeline. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access \"\n./forge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:348:    generated_loc = count_generated_loc(tests_root)\n./forge/utility_scripts/source_context.py:171:        \"discoverArtifactMetadata\",\n./forge/utility_scripts/source_context.py:187:            f\"ERROR: discoverArtifactMetadata failed for {coordinate}. See {log_path_display} for details.\",\n./forge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:87:- the generated test suite is valid, cohesive, and meaningful for the target library\n./forge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:91:- nothing in the generated output suggests the agent solved the task by breaking or trivializing the test\n./forge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:115:Coverage and other metrics do not need a single universal threshold, but they must look credible for the library size and the generated test shape. Suspiciously low coverage, near-empty tests, or inflated metadata with weak tests should be treated as failures that need investigation.\n./forge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:123:- the generated test logic is valid and meaningful\n./forge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:137:- generated tests are trivial, broken, or misleading\n./forge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:158:- describe the important observations from logs, generated tests, and metrics\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:67:7. Use the same finalization path to generate metadata, validate tests, collect stats, and commit.\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:154:  posts a human-intervention comment. Also runs the PR review queues.\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:322:        Disp->>GH: Push preserve branch + human-intervention comment\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:53:| **Dynamic-access report** | JSON written by Gradle task `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` to `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, listing classes and per-class call sites that require dynamic-access metadata, marked covered/uncovered. |\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:9:  - `run(...)`: runs a single generation attempt. It generates the initial dynamic-access report, falls back to `BasicIterativeStrategy` only if no usable guidance exists at the start, otherwise enters the dynamic-access class iteration immediately and counts success only after metadata generation, retest, `generateLibraryStats`, and a commit for the library iteration succeed.\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:212:    Keep -- yes --> KeepOK([Phase returns ok=true,<br/>keep generated tests])\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:234:    GenMD[generateMetadata] --> Test{./gradlew test passes?}\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:274:| Reachability-repo Gradle tasks | `scaffold`, `populateArtifactURLs`, `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`, `test`, `nativeTest`, `generateMetadata`, `generateLibraryStats`. |\n./forge/benchmarks/benchmark_runner.py:71:            \"Forwarded to add_new_library_support.py. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access strategies \"\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:337:def cleanup_generated_test_scaffold(coordinates: str, repo_path: str, metrics_repo_path: str) -> None:\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:362:    cleanup_generated_test_scaffold(coordinates, repo_path, metrics_repo_path)\n./forge/prompt_templates/initial/basic_initial.md:4:You need to generate comprehensive tests for the library defined by these Maven coordinates: {library}.\n./forge/prompt_templates/initial/basic_initial.md:18:- When a test exercises behavior that fundamentally requires open-ended dynamic class loading that Native Image cannot support, such as loading classes, JARs, generated bytecode, plugin implementations, or other class definitions that are only discovered after the native executable is built, catch `Error`, verify it with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` from `org.graalvm.internal.tck`, and re-throw if it does not match. This proves Native Image fails for the right reason instead of skipping the test.\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:23:- Maintain a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files.\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:35:- When a test exercises behavior that fundamentally requires open-ended dynamic class loading that Native Image cannot support, such as loading classes, JARs, generated bytecode, plugin implementations, or other class definitions that are only discovered after the native executable is built, catch `Error`, verify it with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` from `org.graalvm.internal.tck`, and re-throw if it does not match. This proves Native Image fails for the right reason instead of skipping the test.\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md:18:- Maintain a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files.\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md:31:- When a test exercises behavior that fundamentally requires open-ended dynamic class loading that Native Image cannot support, such as loading classes, JARs, generated bytecode, plugin implementations, or other class definitions that are only discovered after the native executable is built, catch `Error`, verify it with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` from `org.graalvm.internal.tck`, and re-throw if it does not match. This proves Native Image fails for the right reason instead of skipping the test.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:89:- Iteratively generate a meaningful, cohesive JUnit test suite for library using AI.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:123:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` keeps generated tests for dynamic-access workflows even if no dynamic-access call sites are covered.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:409:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/workflow_strategy.py:34:    (e.g. scaffold a library, generate metadata, run tests, iterate on fixes).\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:108:                    self._print_dynamic_access_message(\"Coverage not improved. Keeping generated tests by request.\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:388:        \"\"\"Capture tracked and untracked changes under the generated library test tree.\"\"\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/basic_iterative_strategy.py:16:    │   https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/docs/CONTRIBUTING.md#generate-metadata-and-test   │\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/basic_iterative_strategy.py:198:                        f\"Checkpoint generated tests for {self.library} ({unittest_number})\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py:53:            \"   or an unsupported platform feature), remove the generated test that causes that failure.\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py:54:            \"   You may also remove generated test-only files that are only needed by that failing test.\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:77:            \"Iteratively generate and validate unit tests for a given library using the configured agent.\\n\\n\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:141:            \"When using dynamic-access strategies, keep generated tests even when they do not improve \"\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:74:Use the `scaffold` task to generate metadata and test stubs:\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:2:When the repository doesn’t have reachability metadata for a library you are using, the easiest way to generate it is to execute the test suite of the library with the Native Image Agent enabled. The agent is installed together with native-image and can be used to identify elements used during application execution that cannot be discovered by static analysis.\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:26:To run the test task with the agent, run `./gradlew -Pagent` test. This will generate metadata in the build output directory of the project (under `build/native/agent/test`).\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:59:Conditional metadata can be generated by inserting the Native Image Agent options into the command line of the JVM that runs the tests.\n./docs/CI.md:25:  - Uses: generateMatrixBatchedCoordinates to build a matrix (java + os). Runs full tests, pulls only allowed Docker images, then disables Docker networking for deterministic runs.\n./docs/CI.md:28:  - Uses: [`generateChangedMetadataTestMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) with base/head SHAs to test only what changed. It batches each changed metadata version's [`tested-versions`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json) into chunks of up to 30 versions per job, then pulls allowed images, disables Docker networking, validates config, and runs only that batch.\n./docs/CI.md:31:  - Uses: [`generateChangedTestedVersionsMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) to compute only newly added [`tested-versions`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json) from the base/head diff and pairs them with the matching [`metadata-version`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json), then runs [`run-consecutive-tests.sh`](../.github/workflows/scripts/run-consecutive-tests.sh) only for those added versions.\n./docs/CI.md:34:  - Uses: generateInfrastructureChangedCoordinatesMatrix. Pulls allowed images, disables Docker networking, validates config, then runs tests.\n./docs/CI.md:37:  - Uses: generateAffectedSpringTestMatrix to compute impacted Spring AOT projects and produce a matrix; runs triaged native tests via [.github/workflows/scripts/run-spring-aot-triaged-test.sh](../.github/workflows/scripts/run-spring-aot-triaged-test.sh).\n./docs/CI.md:43:  - Uses: [`fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) plus [`generateNewLibraryVersionCompatibilityMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) to build a [`ci.json`](../ci.json)-driven matrix. The matrix generator limits the number of libraries per run, limits each library to at most 30 newer versions per run before expanding across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations, records tested versions only after they pass on every required environment, and creates a single aggregated failure issue per failed library version while preserving the prior failure issue format with added OS and JDK lines.\n./docs/CI.md:49:- [.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml](../.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml): scheduled/manual workflow that generates repository coverage badges and the coverage dashboard from exploded stats files under [stats/](../stats/) and repository [metadata/**/index.json](../metadata/), then force-pushes the published artifacts to the `stats/coverage` branch. The published branch only keeps `latest/badges.json`, `latest/metrics-over-time.svg`, and `history/history.json`.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/ScaffoldTaskTests.java:501:        generatedFiles.addAll(listRelativeFiles(tempDir.resolve(\"tests\")));\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/DiscoverArtifactMetadataTests.java:34:        DiscoverArtifactMetadata task = project.getTasks().create(\"discoverArtifactMetadata\", DiscoverArtifactMetadata.class);\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/DiscoverArtifactMetadataTests.java:65:        DiscoverArtifactMetadata task = project.getTasks().create(\"discoverArtifactMetadata\", DiscoverArtifactMetadata.class);\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle:312:tasks.register(\"discoverArtifactMetadata\", DiscoverArtifactMetadata.class) { task ->\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle:855:// gradle generateAffectedSpringTestMatrix -PbaseCommit=<base> -PnewCommit=<head> -PspringAotBranch=<branch> -PspringAotPath=/path/to/spring-aot-smoke-tests\n./build.gradle:262:    t.setDescription(\"Determines one artifact coordinate via generateInfrastructureChangedCoordinatesMatrix (or uses -Pcoordinate/-Pcoordinates if provided), then runs testInfra for that coordinate and also for 1/64. Options: -Pparallelism to control concurrency.\")\n./tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-daemon-embeddable/2.3.20/build.gradle:12:File generatedTestResourcesDir = layout.buildDirectory.dir(\"generated/test-resources\").get().asFile\n./tests/src/org.jooq/jooq/3.18.2/README.md:7:The generated metadata can be found in the `build/native/agent-output/test` directory.\n./tests/src/org.jooq/jooq/3.18.2/build.gradle:24:        // replace typeReachable value for entries generated by JooqTest test class\n./tests/src/org.jooq/jooq/3.17.7/README.md:7:The generated metadata can be found in the `build/native/agent-output/test` directory.\n./tests/src/org.jooq/jooq/3.17.7/build.gradle:24:        // replace typeReachable value for entries generated by JooqTest test class\n./tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.4.1/README.md:7:The generated metadata can be found in the `build/native/agent-output/test` directory.\n./tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.4.1/build.gradle:22:\t\t// replace typeReachable value for entries generated by LogbackTests test class\n./tests/src/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/6.0.0.Final/build.gradle:32:        // replace typeReachable value for entries generated by AdditionalMetadataTest test class\n./tests/src/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/6.0.0.Final/build.gradle:37:        // replace typeReachable value for entries generated by IdentifierGeneratorTest test class\n./tests/src/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/5.6.14.Final/build.gradle:26:        // replace typeReachable value for entries generated by AdditionalMetadataTest test class\n./tests/src/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/5.6.14.Final/build.gradle:31:        // replace typeReachable value for entries generated by IdentifierGeneratorTest test class\n.